6. Modules 4 & 5: Metadata Extraction and Multi-Format Support

Rich metadata allows the agent to filter the search space before executing semantic matching.

Extraction Logic

Use a structured LLM call to extract metadata from the first 8,000 characters of a document.

class DocumentMetadata(BaseModel):
    title: str
    summary: str
    topics: List[str]
    document_type: str # e.g., 'manual', 'invoice', 'report'
    language: str


Dockling Implementation

Integrate the Dockling library for PDF, DocX, and PowerPoint support.

* Standard Pipeline: Use for high-speed text extraction on standard hardware.
* VLM Pipeline: Use for complex layouts (tables, diagrams). Note: This requires significant VRAM (e.g., RTX 5090 or server-grade GPUs). Local execution of VLMs is recommended for air-gapped or privacy-sensitive builds.


