7. Module 6: Hybrid Search and Re-Ranking

Semantic search alone is insufficient for queries involving specific product codes or acronyms.

Optimization via RRF

Implement Hybrid Search by combining Semantic (Vector) and Keyword (BM25) results using Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF). RRF normalizes the scores from these two disparate search methods, ensuring the most relevant documents rise to the top regardless of whether they were found via similarity or keyword match.

Secondary Re-Ranking

Add a re-ranking step using Cohere or a local Qwen-based re-ranker (e.g., bge-reranker). This model analyzes the top 10–20 results from the hybrid search and re-scores them based on the actual context of the query, significantly reducing the likelihood of the LLM grounding its answer in irrelevant data.


