9. Module 8: Orchestration with Sub-Agents

Complex analysis requires Context Isolation. Loading a 40-page PDF into the main chat window degrades performance and increases costs.

Sub-Agent Design

When the user asks to "Analyze [Document]," the main agent calls the analyze_document tool. A specialized sub-agent is spawned which loads the entire document context (up to 70k+ tokens) to perform its task, returning only the summarized insight to the main agent.

UI Requirements for Reasoning

* Thought Bubbles: Implement a dedicated component to render <think> tags, visually separating the agent’s reasoning from its output.
* Hide/Show Toggle: Allow users to collapse the "Thought Process" for a cleaner interface.
* Nested Tool Indicators: Display nested tool calls with status indicators and green "complete" checkmarks to maintain transparency during long research tasks.


