10. Critical Management: Context and Observability

Context management is the primary failure point in agentic systems.

Monitoring & Token Hygiene

* The 50% Rule: Monitor the status line. If the session consumes >50% of the context window, the agent will likely become sluggish or enter loops. Use /clear to refresh.
* LangSmith Tracing: Use LangSmith to inspect every tool call. Verify the exact SQL generated and the chunks retrieved to diagnose failures.

Beginner’s Troubleshooting Guide

Issue	Diagnosis	Solution
Zero results returned	Overly conservative metadata filtering ("Lazy Prompting").	Update system prompt to prioritize hybrid search over strict filters.
204 / No Content error	Sub-agent failing to resolve a Document ID or File Mapping.	Verify the ID-to-FileName mapping in the analyze_document tool call.
Agent enters a loop	Conflicting tool instructions or degraded context window.	Clear the session (/clear) and provide a more directive prompt.
Slow streaming	Network latency or local model VRAM bottleneck.	Switch from local VLM to Standard Dockling pipeline or cloud-based LLM.


