11. Finalizing the Build: Version Control and Releases

Maintain a rigorous Git workflow to manage the 8-module complexity.

* Incremental Commits: Commit after every successful module validation.
* Tagging: Use semantic tagging (e.g., v0.1 - App Shell, v0.4 - Metadata).
* Alpha Status: The completed build is "Alpha." Before deployment, conduct manual regression testing and establish a formal strategy (Vercel/Cloudflare) for environment variables and migrations.
